        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1960-03-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="[Unnumbered document following Document 710 (#143)]" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d710a-143">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Editor’s Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>—No record has been found of the substance of the discussion at this meeting.
                        <persName corresp="#p_BJN1">Brown</persName>’s diary entry for July 30,
                    however, contains the following reference to it: “… Met with communiqué
                    committee after Foreign Ministers, British and Soviets seemed to like draft.
                        <persName corresp="#p_FW1">Foote</persName> and I had prepared it. All of it
                    had previously been submitted to British. …”</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="superscript">3</hi>
                    <persName corresp="#p_SAA1">Sobolev</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_GSA1">Golunsky</persName> were the Soviet members of this subcommittee (see <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_399">p. 399</ref>), but it is not
                    known who represented the Soviet Union at this meeting.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
